section.section:
The form shall clearly and concisely explain in 10 point boldface type:
the nature, extent, and cost of the coverage that would be provided under the policy if not waived by the first named insured;
each effect of a waiver as stated in subsection (b) of this section;
that a failure of the first named insured to make a waiver requires an insurer to provide the coverage described in § 19-505 of this subtitle;
that an insurer may not refuse to underwrite a person because the person refuses to waive the coverage described in § 19-505 of this subtitle; and
that a waiver made under this section must be an affirmative written waiver.
